COMMAND : diag sniffer packet any 'src host <SOURCEIP> and dst host <DESTINATIONIP> and port <PORT>'

EXAMPLE : diag sniffer packet any 'src host 192.168.1.99 and dst host 192.168.1.1 and port 22'

EXPLANATION :

<SOURCEIP>        Source IP of the packet
<DESTINATIONIP>   Destination IP of the packet
<PORT>            Used port of the packet
